message.content:
<OUTPUT_TEXT>
To involve parent volunteers and older students in children's activities and facilitate focused, complex play, start by organizing regular play-based learning sessions where parents and older students are invited to participate as helpers or play partners. Provide them with guidance and training on how to scaffold children's play, ask open-ended questions, and encourage problem-solving. Assign specific roles, such as leading a small group, setting up materials, or modeling cooperative play. Rotate responsibilities so everyone has a chance to engage with different children and activities. Encourage reflection and feedback after sessions to continuously improve the experience and ensure it remains meaningful and developmentally appropriate for all participants.
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
